{
  "id": 6024844719947776,
  "name": "WebAssembly Custom Descriptors",
  "summary": "Allows WebAssembly to store data associated with source-level types more efficiently in new \"custom descriptor\" objects. These custom descriptors can be configured with prototypes for the WebAssembly objects of that source-level type. This allows methods to be installed on a WebAssembly object's prototype chain and called directly from JS using normal method call syntax. The prototypes and methods can be configured declaratively using an imported builtin function.",
